  "prompt": "Where did the name Twitter come from?",
  "response": "The name **Twitter** was inspired by the sound and concept of birds chirping, symbolizing quick, short, and frequent bursts of communication. The company's founders, Jack Dorsey, Biz Stone, and Evan Williams, wanted a name that reflected the platform's core purpose: enabling users to share brief, real-time updates.\n\nThe word \"twitter\" itself refers to the **short, high-pitched sounds made by birds**, which aligned with the idea of \"tweeting\" short messages. The team also considered other names, such as **\"Status\"** and **\"Twitch,\"** but ultimately chose \"Twitter\" because it felt more lively and engaging. The domain name **twitter.com** was already taken when they decided on the name, so they purchased it from its previous owner.",
